<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-14T10:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-14T10:40:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1704.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-14T11:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1915—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Horacista Bonneti shot and killed General Ricart, chief of the
                            President’s bodyguard, yesterday afternoon. As a result, political
                            feeling runs high. Bonneti is cousin of Tejera who, with Vidal, shot
                                Cáceres.<note n="2" xml:id="d258fn2">See <ref target="frus1911#pg_174">For Rel. 1911, p. 174</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>